{"id":1267977797,"question_id":653,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1Â month","timestamp":1716688580,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"23 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1267977797/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"45.2 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * public class TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode left;\n *     TreeNode right;\n *     TreeNode() {}\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\n *         this.val = val;\n *         this.left = left;\n *         this.right = right;\n *     }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    boolean res = false;\n    void dfs(TreeNode cur, int k, List<Integer> al){\n        if(res == true || cur == null)\n            return;\n        \n        if(al.contains(k-cur.val)){\n            res = true;\n            return;\n        }\n        \n        al.add(cur.val);\n        \n        dfs(cur.left, k, al);\n        dfs(cur.right, k, al);\n    }\n    public boolean findTarget(TreeNode root, int k) {\n        List<Integer> al = new ArrayList<>();\n        \n        dfs(root, k, al);\n\n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
